body_html:
Yes, its a fix for compiler warning.
We are trying to use the same header and it causes build break for our code .

[ 71s] /usr/include/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/interpreter.h: In member function 'const std::pair<TfLiteNode, TfLiteRegistration>* tflite::Interpreter::node_and_registration(int) const':
[ 71s] /usr/include/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/interpreter.h:212:20: error: comparison between signed and unsigned integer expressions [-Werror=sign-compare]
[ 71s] if (node_index >= nodes_and_registration.size() || node_index < 0)
[ 71s]

cast in the interior function is an option.
but there are other places in the same file where the datatype is changed instead of a cast . Please check the below patch.

FYI: Convert int -> size_t so that implicit conversion doesn't lose integer precision

body:
Yes, its a fix for compiler warning.
We are trying to use the same header and it causes build break for our code .

> 

> [   71s] /usr/include/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/interpreter.h: In member function 'const std::pair<TfLiteNode, _TfLiteRegistration>* tflite::Interpreter::node_and_registration(int) const':
[   71s] /usr/include/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/interpreter.h:212:20: **error: comparison between signed and unsigned integer expressions [-Werror=sign-compare]**
[   71s]      if (node_index >= nodes_and_registration_.size() || node_index < 0)
[   71s]

cast in the interior function is an option.
but there are other places in the same file where the datatype is changed instead of a cast . Please check the below patch.

> FYI:   **Convert int -> size_t so that implicit conversion doesn't lose integer precision**
